
We have notifications and priority, these are getting multiplied and leading to
class explosion. To avoid this, we can use the Bridge design pattern to separate
the notification types from the priority levels. This way, we can create a more
 flexible and maintainable system.
 We create notification types (e.g., EmailNotification, SMSNotification) and
 priority levels (e.g., HighPriority, LowPriority) as separate classes. The
  notification classes will have a reference to the priority level, allowing us
to mix and match them without creating a new class for every combination.